ğŸ¯ Goal
Create EC2 Instance using Terraform + GitHub Actions
Git push chesthe automatic ga EC2 create avvali in AWS.

Use:
HashiCorp Terraform
GitHub
GitHub Actions
Amazon Web Services

âœ… STEP 1: Install Required Tools (Local System)

Check:
terraform -v
aws --version
git --version

Install ayyi undali.

âœ… STEP 2: Create Terraform Project
mkdir terraform-ec2
cd terraform-ec2
code .

âœ… STEP 3: Create main.tf
Create file â†’ main.tf

Paste:

provider "aws" {
  region = "ap-south-1"
}

resource "aws_instance" "myec2" {
  ami           = "ami-0f5ee92e2d63afc18"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  tags = {
    Name = "Github-Actions-EC2"
  }
}


âš ï¸ Note: AMI Mumbai region ki correct undali.

âœ… STEP 4: Test Locally Once (Important)
terraform init
terraform apply

EC2 create ayithe confirm chesukoni:

terraform destroy

âœ… STEP 5: Create GitHub Repository
Go to:

ğŸ‘‰ GitHub
Create new repository.

âœ… STEP 6: Push Code to GitHub
Inside project folder run:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial Terraform code"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin <your-repo-url>
git push -u origin main

âœ… STEP 7: Add AWS Secrets in GitHub

GitHub Repo â†’ Settings â†’ Secrets â†’ Actions â†’ New repository secret
Add 3 secrets:

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
AWS_REGION


Example:
AWS_REGION â†’ ap-south-1

âœ… STEP 8: Create GitHub Actions Workflow File
Inside your project create folders:

.github/workflows/

Inside that create:

terraform.yml

âœ… STEP 9: Paste Workflow Code
name: Terraform EC2 Deploy

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  terraform:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
    - name: Checkout Code
      uses: actions/checkout@v3

    - name: Setup Terraform
      uses: hashicorp/setup-terraform@v2

    - name: Configure AWS Credentials
      uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v2
      with:
        aws-access-key-id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}
        aws-secret-access-key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}
        aws-region: ${{ secrets.AWS_REGION }}

    - name: Terraform Init
      run: terraform init

    - name: Terraform Apply
      run: terraform apply -auto-approve

âœ… STEP 10: Push Workflow File
git add .
git commit -m "Added GitHub Actions workflow"
git push

ğŸ‰ FINAL RESULT

Push jarigina ventane:

1ï¸âƒ£ GitHub Actions trigger avuthundi
2ï¸âƒ£ Terraform init run avuthundi
3ï¸âƒ£ Terraform apply run avuthundi
4ï¸âƒ£ EC2 create avuthundi in AWS

Check in:
ğŸ‘‰ Amazon EC2 console
